Starting with four characteristics: PSAatPET, PSAdt, Gleason and RT1oTTO (RT as first treament, yes or no).

However, we work with those variables categorized.

 PET         PSAatPET         PSAdt    Gleason RT1oTTO

Performing variable selection through the AIC (Akaike information criterion) measure, we see that PSAatPET and Gleason are not statistically significant when the goal is to explain the variability of PET/CT-PSMA.

term estimate std.error statistic p.value
(Intercept) 1.1923 0.5318 2.2419 0.0250
PSAdt>10 meses 1.1089 0.6379 1.7383 0.0822
RT1oTTO -1.8698 0.6382 -2.9301 0.0034

The intercept is the reference level. Here, PSAdt=<10meses and RT1oTTO=0.

Before some interpretations, lets see some graphs to check the model fit quality. The residuals in its most simple idea is the diference between the observed and the expected (fitted). In A we should expect all std residuals to be between the (-3, 3) interval. If outside, we have evidence of outliers presence. In the other graphs, in black we show the model fit. The ideal scenario would be a steady line on zero. We have here a behavior similar to that, so our model is well fitted/adequate/suitable.

The following graph shows what is called confusion matrix. We basically predict the outputs based on the probabilities returned by the model and compare it with the reality (the data). In the off main-diagonal we have the hits. We can also summarize all that through the accuracy measure. Here, it is of 73%.

Interpretando os coeficientes

   (Intercept) PSAdt>10 meses        RT1oTTO 
      1.192268       1.108920      -1.869841

The logistic regression return the log odds. Nevertheless, those values do not have a precise or meaningful interpretation. We can convert the default log odds into probabilities through the logistic function

\[ \text{Logistic function}(X\beta) = \frac{e^{X\beta}}{1 + e^{X\beta}}. \]

The default probability (PSAdt=<10meses and RT1oTTO=0) of PET/CS-PSMA is

[1] 0.7671465

Changing just the PSAdt to >10meses or just the RT1oTTO to 1, will change the probability to

[1] 0.9089754
[1] 0.3368033

respectively.

BY changing both the probability goes to

[1] 0.6061954

Another possibility is looking to the odds ratios. An odds of 1 equivalent to a probability of 0.5.

Changing just the PSAdt to >10meses or just the RT1oTTO to 1, will get odds of

[1] 3.031083
[1] 0.1541482

respectively. i.e., by going to >10meses the odds is three times bigger (a 300% increase) and going to RToTTO=1 will decrease the odds (a 85% decrease).

By changing both the odds goes to

[1] 0.4672359

a 53% decrease.
